wiki.content: Returning to their trademark dance-pop sound after a fiery collaboration with NGHTMRE on “Save Yourself,” The Chainsmokers team up with country singer Kelsea Ballerini for their latest hit. The song also features frequent collaborator Emily Warren as a songwriter. The track was first announced in an Instagram post five days prior to the release of the song. It’s about someone in a relationship. They feel with their heart that a certain person is who they want and are trying to explain why, but the people in their life think that the relationship is not good for them anyway–saying they should think with their head and not their heart. It’s hard to say whether or not the relationship is actually bad, or if everyone on the outside just thinks it is because of some kind of bias. “Here’s a song we wrote about being yourself and not giving a fuck what people think about you” -Andrew Taggart on his Instagram profile, @drewtaggart “This song in particular holds a very special place with me because it’s something I experienced personally this year and I’m sure a lot of others have as well. Life is complex and unexpected. We are challenged daily with new struggles that don’t always feel right or seem like it will ever get better, people will always tell you what they think, but life has taught me one thing which is to always follow your heart because that is where you will find happiness. Which I am lucky enough to have so much. I hope you love this song as much as we do and all do the same in following your heart in whatever way feels right” -Alex Pall on his Instagram profile, @alexpall As of the week ending January 12, 2019, “This Feeling” peaked at #50 on the Hot 100 and #4 on the Hot Dance Songs chart.
